item.description:
arXiv:2502.14725v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: In this paper, we study the time-space fractional differential equation of the Volterra type:
  \begin{align*}
  {D}^\alpha_{0 \vert t} (u) +(-\Delta_N)^{\sigma}u &= u(1+au-bu^2)-au\int_0^t {K}(t-s) u(\cdot) \, ds,
  \end{align*}
  where $a,b>0$ are given constants, $\alpha,\sigma \in (0,1)$, equipped with a homogeneous Neumann's boundary condition and a positive initial data. The boundedness and uniform continuity of the solution on the entire $\mathbb{R}^+$ are established. Moreover, the asymptotic behavior of the positive solution is investigated.
